Question #4 - Part A

Sean Lahman complied a comprehensive database containing pitching, hitting, and fielding statistics from all Major League Baseball games from 1871 through 2016. The database is available in the package Lahman and contains several tables.

  • The data frame People contains one row per unique player for a 20,370 current and former MLB players.
  • The data frame Batting contains player performance data for each season (year). It contains 110,495 observations, as most of the players in People have careers spanning several years.
# install.packages("Lahman")
library(Lahman)
data("People")
data("Batting")

That is, find all unique players who have achieved 40 steals, SB, and 40 home runs, HR in the same season. Be sure that players who have achieved the 40/40 standard in multiple seasons only appear in your list once. Print the number of rows in your final data frame.
